    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Officials in any of the senior grades of the former imperial Chinese civil service. Mandarins were chosen by examination, and there were nine grades, each of which was distinguished by a distinctive round ornament or button on top of the official headgear.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
